# ParakeetX Standalone API With Diarization

## Summary
Build a fresh FastAPI server inspired by [whisperx-api-server](https://github.com/Nyralei/whisperx-api-server/tree/main), using `nvidia/parakeet-tdt-0.6b-v2` through NeMo for ASR and optional `pyannote-audio` diarization for speaker labels, following the WhisperX diarization pattern from [m-bain/whisperX](https://github.com/m-bain/whisperX). Use `uv` for all Python dependency management, not `pip`.

## Key Changes
- Scaffold `src/parakeetx_api_server/` with config, auth, routers, model managers, audio normalization, transcription, diarization, speaker assignment, and response formatters.
- Add `.mise.toml`, `pyproject.toml`, `uv.lock`, README, `.env.example`, `Dockerfile.cpu`, `Dockerfile.cuda`, and `compose.yaml`.
- Use `mise` tasks that call `uv sync`, `uv run pytest`, and `uv run uvicorn`; Dockerfiles install `uv` and use `uv sync --frozen`.
- Normalize uploads to 16 kHz mono WAV before inference.
- Cache Parakeet and pyannote models separately, with explicit load/list/unload endpoints and CUDA cleanup on unload.

## Public API
- `POST /v1/audio/transcriptions` supports OpenAI-style multipart fields: `file`, `model`, `language`, `response_format`, `timestamp_granularities[]`, `stream`, `diarize`, `min_speakers`, `max_speakers`, `num_speakers`, `speaker_embeddings`, and `highlight_words`.
- Parakeet provides transcript text plus native word/segment timestamps; no WhisperX forced-alignment stage is needed.
- When `diarize=true`, run `pyannote/speaker-diarization-community-1`, requiring `HF_TOKEN` and accepted Hugging Face model terms.
- Assign speaker IDs to words and segments by maximum time-overlap between pyannote diarization intervals and Parakeet word/segment timestamps, matching WhisperX’s speaker-label approach.
- `verbose_json` includes `segments[].speaker`, `segments[].words[].speaker`, and raw diarization segments; subtitle outputs prefix cues with speaker labels when available.
- Unsupported features fail clearly: `/v1/audio/translations` returns `501`; non-English language requests, streaming, prompt biasing, temperature sampling, hotwords, and forced alignment return `422` when requested.

## Config
- Core env vars: `API_KEY`, `API_KEYS_FILE`, `HF_TOKEN`, `PARAKEET__MODEL_NAME`, `PARAKEET__DEVICE`, `PARAKEET__PRELOAD_MODEL`, `PARAKEET__LOCAL_FILES_ONLY`, `DIARIZATION__MODEL_NAME`, `DIARIZATION__DEVICE`, `DIARIZATION__PRELOAD_MODEL`, `MAX_CONCURRENT_TRANSCRIPTIONS`, `UVICORN_HOST`, and `UVICORN_PORT`.
- Default Parakeet model: `nvidia/parakeet-tdt-0.6b-v2`.
- Default diarization model: `pyannote/speaker-diarization-community-1`.
- Default diarization behavior: off unless `diarize=true`.

## Test Plan
- Unit tests for config parsing, API-key auth, unsupported-feature failures, model aliasing, response formatting, diarization interval conversion, and overlap-based speaker assignment.
- Route tests with FastAPI `TestClient` and generated WAV fixtures, monkeypatching Parakeet and pyannote model calls so normal tests do not download models.
- Integration tests guarded by `RUN_PARAKEET_INTEGRATION=1` and `RUN_DIARIZATION_INTEGRATION=1`.
- Verify with `mise run test`, then optionally `docker compose --profile cpu build` and `docker compose --profile cuda build`.

## Assumptions
- Implement from scratch rather than copying GPL upstream API-server source.
- Keep this version standalone only: no Kafka/S3 distributed workers.
- Commit `uv.lock` for reproducible installs.
- Preserve the existing untracked `.codex` file.
- Initialize CodeGraph after the scaffold exists.
